Japanese Finance Minister Kiichi Miyazawaexpects the dollar to rebound soon, a Ministry spokesman said.    He quoted Miyazawa as telling Japanese reporters that majorindustrial nations are aggressively intervening in currencymarkets worldwide to prevent a dollar free-fall.    The minister believes that market forces will push thedollar back up from its record low of 144.70 yen today,according to the spokesman.    Miyazawa told the Japanese reporters the U.S. Unit fellbecause Japanese investors sold dollars to hedge currency risksbefore the close of the 1986/87 fiscal year on March 31. REUTER&#3;